I therefore support this report , which will enable the European Union to anticipate potential food crises , which are in connection with animal origin , more predictable and better responding to them .
I voted in favour of this report because , for example , we in Romania and in other Member States are sometimes affected by crises arising from animal by-products , which pose a risk for human and animal health , such as transnational spongious forums , Encepopathie , Dioxxin , swine flu and mouth .
Such crises can also have greater , adverse effects on the socio-economic situation of farmers and industrial sectors affected , as well as a reduction in consumption confidence in the safety of animal products .
There can also be an adverse impact on the environment : eradication of cadality and biodiversity .
We had to review the regulation of animal by-products , which are not intended for human consumption , from a legal perspective .
This will therefore solve the problems arising from a different interpretation of the regulation and , in turn , the problems that arise : distortions of competition and differing protection against health risks of humans and animals ; classification of animal products , which is based on comprehensive risks ; clarifying derogations ( for example , the impact of animal products on research , illness , natural disasters ; reducing customs duties through certain professional conditions .
The review maintains the principles used in the EU for regulating the use , processing , traceability and distribution of non-human consumption products , thereby ensuring a high standard of food safety and consumer protection .
