The Commission &apos; s present report aims to provide a basis for analysing and waking any change in the uniform system of the medium-term financial assistance .
This financing system is implemented by Article 119 of the EC Treaty , which is the third stage of economic and monetary union , only for which Member States are not joining the common currency .
Once again , the system was examined in October 1997 on the basis of a report drawn up by the Commission .
At the time when the Council approved the Commission &apos; s position to maintain the system and faster the decision that a renewed review should be carried out after the same procedure , in the light of changes relating to the beginning of the third stage .
Accordingly , the Commission must submit a report to the Council so that this system can reexamine once again .
The report contains three main recommendations .
The first recommendation : the uniform system should be maintained as an instrument for implementing Article 119 of the Treaty , which continues to be applicable to the Member States involved in the euro area ; as long as these Member States cannot join the single currency , they can , along with all the new members of the Community , cope with their balance of payments and thus have a desire to mobilise this system .
Given the current standard of economic , financial and monetary integration , the likelihood that some Member States may face difficulties with their balance of payments is extremely low from the institutional point of view , but the system must remain in force .
The second recommendation : the possibility of applying loans from other Member States to fund the loans granted under the system should be abolished , because it has never been used for different reasons .
In future , the return to the capital market should remain the only possible option .
Third and last recommendation : the reduction in the number of Member States currently applying this form of financial support , as well as the need to cover the potential needs of new Member States , justifies the reduction in the intervention fund intended for the system of EUR 16 to 12 billion .
